</p>
<p align=justify><font color=maroon>
The Lost Camels of Tartary tells the remarkable story of John Hare's four journeys, when he ventured into territory unseen for more than fifty years. &nbsp; Entrusting his life to a colourful cast of companions, he braves bandit attacks, ferocious sandstorms, a missing caravan of domestic camels, shares a wild camel calf' s first few hours, tracks the equally endangered Gobi Bear and happens upon Tu-ying, ancient outpost of the lost city of Lou Lan. &nbsp; A compelling account of desert adventure, wildlife conservation and international diplomacy in one of the world' s last great wildernesses, this is a classic record of modern day exploration.
</p>
