<h4><u>Reading the Landscape</u></h4>
<font color=maroon>
<p align=justify>
This special issue (vol.31) of the <font color=indigo><i>SAGT Journal</i></font> (ISSN 0140-2862) contains 112 pages, 26 photographs, and 48 diagrams of illustrated updates on landscape research. &nbsp; It is published jointly by the Scottish Association of Geography Teachers and the Royal Scottish Geographical Society, and incorporates the papers from the Council of British Geography Seminar on Reading the Landscape, which took place at Stirling University on June 22/23 2002.
</p>
<p align=justify><b><font color=black>
This publication is available to SAGT, RSGS, and GA members at a discount price of &pound;10.00 including postage and packing. &nbsp; The price for non-members is &pound;12.00 including postage and packing. &nbsp; <font color=black>Ref. WORL.
</b></p>
</td></tr></table>
