<a name="Glasgow"><hr></a>
<br>
<table width=100%><tr>
<td width=80%><font color=green>
<h4><u>Discovering Cities : Glasgow</u></h4>
<font color=maroon>
<p align=justify>
This series published by the Geographical Association aims to enable urban explorers to make the most of visits to modern cities of the British Isles, whether for educational or recreational reasons. &nbsp; Background information on the geographical, historical, economic, and political factors which have shaped the growth of each city is provided, and urban trails guide students and visitors around areas of particular interest.
<br><br>
Primarily for post-16 geography students, and their teachers, undertaking urban fieldwork in these areas, the guides aim to give a sense of place and an appreciation of a fascinating and often undervalued physical environment, but should also be of interest to the general reader, and to visitors who wish to have more than a superficial understanding of these areas.
<br><br>
The author of this particular booklet in the series is Professor <font color=red>Michael Pacione<font color=maroon> of the Department of Geography of the University of Strathclyde. &nbsp; ISBN 1-903448-88-3.
<br><br>
<font color=black><b>
Full price direct from RSGS:&nbsp; &pound;9.99<br>
RSGS members' price:&nbsp; &pound;6.00 (both excluding postage and packing).</b>
</p></td>
<td width=20% align=center><img src="images/glasgow.jpg" alt="Glasgow" height=240 width=120></td>
</tr></table>
