<font color=green>
<h4><u>RSGS Calendar</u></h4>
<table width=100% cellpadding=5><tr>
<td width=70%>
<font color=maroon>
<p align=justify>
The <font color=indigo><i>RSGS Calendar 2005</i></font> continues in previous years' successful format, compiling some of the best photographs of Scotland's remarkable scenery and geography into this prestigious publication. &nbsp; As usual it draws both on the extensive RSGS photographic collection, and material submitted to the Society's <font color=indigo><i>Photographer of the Year</i></font> competition.
</p>
<p align=justify>
The &quot;booklet&quot;-style calendar is formatted as 16 printed pages, each measuring 240mm (approx. 9&#189; inches) square. &nbsp; It is printed on top quality art paper, with a gloss laminated cover, and is supplied with a strong envelope.
</p>
<p align=justify>
The front cover (illustrated opposite) is backed with an information page outlining the Society's role as the foremost independent geographical body in Scotland. &nbsp; This is followed by 12 month-to-view calendar pages. &nbsp; Each page contains a stunning shot, plus the calendar for the current, previous, and forthcoming months, plus a useful notes section. &nbsp; RSGS contact information is printed on the back cover.
</p></td>
<td width=30% valign=top>
<img src="images/calendar.jpg" alt="Calendar" height=240 width=240></td>
</tr><tr>
<td width=100% colspan=2>
<p align=justify><font color=maroon>
In spite of a modest price increase, we hope that you will feel you can support the RSGS by purchasing calendars, not only for yourself, but also as a seasonal gift for your family and friends.
</p>
<p align=justify>
Weighing 96 grams (including envelope), the calendar is economical for mailing, and we are sure that, with 12 stunning Scottish scenes, it would be a prized gift for family and friends, especially those overseas.
</p>
<p align=justify><font color=black>
<b>Calendars are priced at &pound;4.00 each</b>, and will be available for purchase at Society meetings. &nbsp; Otherwise they may be ordered directly from RSGS headquarters, in which case <b>packaging and postage will be charged at 40p per copy</b>.
</p>
</td>
</tr></table>
